      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TOUGH ENOUGH (1) is generally an honest type in the frame at 16 of 37 starts but missed the placings last time when fourth (19.00) over 350m at this track. Solid record here winning three races. Looks a key player drawing the cherry. GOLDSTAR CRYSTAL (2) turned in a plain effort last time when sixth at this track over 300m behind Sweet Legs (17.05) in a Grade 5. Smart beginner who should take advantage of the low draw. One of the better hopes. NOT THE DEPUTY (8) returned a better run last time, finishing in the money (20.18) at Capalaba behind Aussie Puzzle in a P5. Turned chasing the leaders but kept coming. Some good form is emerging from his last run. Leading chance. KING'S SHADOW (7) was prominent throughout when successful last start. Must be respected.",
